<div class="page">
  <h1>Health and Wellbeing</h1>
  <p>Several workspaces in the <a class="repo-link" href="/?category=health">Health &amp; Wellbeing</a> category use Claude to manage personal health data. The <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-health-helper/">Claude Health Helper</a> provides a general health documentation workspace, while <a class="repo-link" href="/repos/claude-therapy-tracker/">Claude Therapy Tracker</a> focuses specifically on therapy session notes and progress tracking.</p>
  <p>These workspaces highlight an advantage of the terminal-based approach: your health data stays local on your machine. There's no cloud service, no account, no third-party data processing. Claude works with files on your filesystem, and nothing leaves your computer unless you explicitly push it somewhere.</p>
  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;"><a href="/?category=health" style="font-weight: 500;">Browse all Health repositories &rarr;</a></div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>
